ISLAMABAD, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan strongly condemned the attack at a temple in the Afghan capital Kabul that resulted in the loss of lives and injuries to many others on Saturday. "Pakistan reiterates its condemnation of terrorism in all forms and manifestations," the Pakistani Ministry of Foreign Affairs said in a statement. The statement also expressed Pakistan's strong solidarity with the people of Afghanistan and support for all efforts of the Afghan authorities in fighting the menace of terrorism and ensuring the protection of the public.  â– 